BORQUEZ, LAWSON SELECT COLLEGES 
Sprinter Tony Borquez of Alemany High and distance runner Craig Lawson of 
Granada Hills High will attend USC and Brigham Young, respectively, in the 
fall. 
Borquez, eighth in the 400 meters in last year's state championships, signed a 
letter of intent Wednesday. He also considered UCLA and Cal State Northridge. 
Lawson, the City Section cross-country champion, will attend BYU on an academic 
scholarship. 
